<html> 
    <head> 
        <title>Javascript string methods</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h2>Javascript string methods</h2>
        <p>the string() method is used to convert a number to a string.</p> 
        <p id="numresult"></p>
        <p id="stringresults"></p>
        <script>
        var x = 11;
        var y = 22; 

        document.getElementById("numresult").innerHTML = x + y;
        document.getElementById("stringresults").innerHTML = String(x) + String(y); 
        </script>
    </body>
</html>    